  "text": "Such scenarios arise, in particular, for integrating databases across the Internet, or the so-called \"deep Web.\" Our recent study [CITATION_1] in April 2004 estimated 450,000 online databases. With the virtually unlimited amount of information, the deep Web is clearly an important frontier for data integration. On this deep Web, numerous online databases provide data via their query interfaces, instead of static URL links. Each query interface accepts queries over its query schemas (e.g., author, title, subject, ... for amazon.com). Schema matching across Web interfaces is essential for mediating queries across deep Web sources.",
